{
  "_description": "CBAM (Carbon Border Adjustment Mechanism) exposure example. Two scenarios share an identical K-ETS market structure — tightening cap, free-allocation phase-out, rising EUA reference price — but differ only in whether participants export to CBAM-covered markets. In 'No CBAM Exposure' all cbam_export_share values are zero, so no additional liability appears. In 'With CBAM Exposure' the Steel sector exports 40 % of its output to the EU and Petrochemical exports 30 %, creating a growing CBAM liability as the EUA–KAU gap widens. Compare the 'CBAM Liability' and 'Total Cost incl. CBAM' columns to quantify the cross-border carbon cost burden on each sector.",
